body:
We cannot fix this crash because there is no way to debug it after-the-fact. The crash happens because SIGSEGV arrives to the process unexpectedly. This may be cause by memory issue, weird cgo memory corruption, or even a hardware issue. There is no way to know what the issue is from the stack trace.

@niklasf119 Please open another issue if you get more crashes like this. I will close this one for now because there is no way for us to act.

Please also consider running memtest.
